  "prompt": "In my room I have birds, photography and plants what should I use instead of cityscapes?",
  "response": "Since your room features birds, photography, and plants, you might want to consider incorporating nature or wildlife themes instead of cityscapes. Here are a few ideas:\n\n1. **Forest Landscapes**: These can complement the natural elements of plants and bird motifs.\n2. **Mountain Scenes**: These provide a sense of adventure and awe that pairs well with the beauty of nature.\n3. **Ocean or Beach Views**: These can add a serene and tranquil vibe to your room, aligning with the natural theme.\n4. **Floral Photography**: Highlighting close-up shots of flowers and plants can enhance your existing plant collection.\n5. **Wildlife Photography**: Featuring animals in their natural habitat can resonate with both the birds and the plant life in your room.\n6. **Botanical Prints**: Detailed illustrations of various plants and flowers can add an elegant touch.\n7. **Sky and Celestial Images**: Depictions of the sky, stars, and celestial bodies can provide a dreamy, expansive feeling.\n\nChoose artwork or decorative elements that reflect the natural theme and bring cohesion to your space, ensuring your room feels harmonious and well-curated.",
